rComments: Extremely arrogant, invites you to talk to him at the end of lecture but then has no time for you. Doesn't seem like he's interested in teaching at all he should just be doing research.
Professor Savaria is really helpful.

A very nice guy. Although his notes and lectures are not the best, he still manages to make QM fairly interesting. It's hard to teach QM as I felt most people in the course just plain hate physics in the first place, so obviously they are going to hate the prof. His problem sets and exam were extremely fair, more practice problems would be nice.
Absolutely worst professor ever. Worst notes, worst lectures, and just plain arrogant.

Really isn't interesting in teaching, and therefore shouldn't be doing it. His philosophy, according to him: "You should feel confused after my lectures so you're more motivated to go home and study the material yourself." He's not just bad at explaining stuff, he just doesn't do that at all.
